name: Tropicana implosion
summary: The iconic Tropicana Las Vegas casino is set to be demolished in a spectacular implosion. The demolition, which will be broadcast live, is scheduled for today and is expected to be a breathtaking spectacle. Residents near the casino have planned to watch the implosion from their homes, while tourists in nearby hotels will have a front-row seat to the event. The implosion will pave the way for a new era in Las Vegas, with plans to develop a baseball stadium on the site. The demolition is reminiscent of other historic Las Vegas hotel implosions, which have become synonymous with the city's ever-evolving skyline.

name: Robert Saleh
summary: The New York Jets have fired head coach Robert Saleh after a disappointing start to the 2022 season. Saleh had a record of 20-36 in three-plus seasons with the Jets. There were reports that Saleh considered firing offensive coordinator Nathaniel Hackett before he was fired himself. Saleh was escorted out of the building by the director of security after he was fired. Jeff Ulbrich will take over as interim head coach. The Jets owner hopes that firing Saleh will bring "new energy" to the team. Saleh was reportedly "blindsided" by the firing. Some have questioned whether firing Saleh will solve the issues for the Jets, who have been struggling for years.

name: Geoffrey Hinton
summary: Geoffrey Hinton, a former CMU faculty member, and his colleague John Hopfield have been awarded the 2024 Nobel Prize in Physics for their groundbreaking research in artificial intelligence (AI). Hinton, known as the "Godfather of AI," has made significant contributions to the field and has raised concerns about the potential risks of AI, known as X-risk. Hinton's work on artificial neural networks has laid the foundation for modern AI and machine learning applications. Despite his accolades, Hinton remains cautious about the potential dangers of AI and has emphasized the need for responsible development and regulation.

name: Coldplay
summary: Coldplay, the iconic British rock band, has announced an extensive 2025 North America tour, including highly anticipated performances at Stanford Stadium on May 31, Gillette Stadium, Sun Bowl, Camp Randall Stadium, and many other venues. Tickets for these shows are now on sale, with some fans even resorting to contacting police due to missing out on tickets in India. The tour adds 10 new dates to Coldplay's already extensive Music of the Spheres World Tour, which has been praised for its immersive and captivating live experience. Additionally, Coldplay has launched an exclusive in-app experience on TikTok called "MOON MUSiC," offering fans a unique behind-the-scenes look at the band's music and performances.

name: Peter Todd
summary: A recent HBO documentary has claimed that Peter Todd, a former Bitcoin developer, is the pseudonymous creator of Bitcoin, Satoshi Nakamoto. However, hours before the documentary aired, Todd denied these allegations. Despite Todd's denial, the documentary, titled "The Inventor: Out for Blood in Silicon Valley," has prompted speculation about Todd's potential involvement in the creation of Bitcoin. Various media outlets, including CoinDesk, Forbes, Benzinga, and Bloomberg, have reported on the documentary's claims and Todd's subsequent denial. The documentary suggests that Todd's technical expertise and personal history align with the characteristics of Satoshi Nakamoto, but Todd maintains that he is not the creator of Bitcoin. The true identity of Satoshi Nakamoto remains a mystery, and the HBO documentary's claims have sparked renewed interest in the ongoing quest to uncover the person behind Bitcoin's creation.

name: Melania Trump
summary: Melania Trump's upcoming memoir has sparked significant attention, with various news outlets highlighting her stance on abortion rights. The Guardian US reports that Trump passionately defends abortion rights, while The Washington Post notes that her memoir is unique among first lady memoirs. Abortion, Every Day emphasizes Trump's self-proclaimed passionate support for pro-choice views. Vanity Fair criticizes the book as poorly written but packed with content. CNN's request for an interview with Trump was met with a $250,000 request from her book publisher. BBC highlights five takeaways from the book, including Trump's support for abortion rights. NBC News and Al Jazeera English also report on Trump's pro-choice stance, which differs from her husband's views. POLITICO states that Trump signals support for abortion rights, emphasizing that there is "no room for compromise" on the issue. TIME shares Trump's views on abortion and her husband's reaction. Overall, these headlines indicate that Melania Trump's memoir has garnered attention for her expressed support for abortion rights, which is a departure from her husband's stance.
